I"<p>The growth and popularity of sketchnoting, a practice of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/virtual-reality-renders-abstract-concepts-into-tangible-objects">making abstract concepts more tangible</a> through <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/description-and-depiction-are-interconnected">depictions, rather than descriptions</a>, strongly signals the existence latent visual reasoning capabilities. This <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-movement-supports-spatial-reasoning">other form of knowledge</a> can be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-should-amplify-fundamental-capabilities">amplified</a> in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-interface-users-with-knowledge">knowledge work</a>.</p>
